Commentary Text: Ashwin to Watson, out Caught by Sam Curran!! Watson has picked out cow corner - the longest part of this ground - and Ashwin knows this, so ends up bowling a carrom ball forcing him to go across the line and against the spin. But once a Watto commitment stays a Watto commitment, ending up in the slog sweep leading to a big top-edge, which Curran - a cool few yards inside the boundary - runs across to gather. Watson c Sam Curran b Ashwin 26(24) [4s-3 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Kuggeleijn to Rahul, out Caught by Jadeja!! Kuggeleijn's first wicket in the IPL is a huge one of Rahul. This is a match-changing event for sure. Rahul was waiting for the seamers to come on. And it was a given that he will go after them. He sets himself to slog this one out of the park. Kuggeleijn again is smart enough to bowl an off-cutter. He gets the desired help from the deck and Rahul's timing was in a mess on the slog. He could only hit it to deep mid-wicket and Jadeja there makes no mistake. He takes it with utmost ease. Rahul c Jadeja b Kuggeleijn 55(47) [4s-3 6s-1]
